(1)
69th Place (right, beyond body of water), south from Calamus Ave., showing the Sedgewick House (tower thereon), said to have been built in the 1870's. It was still standing in 1934.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, viewed southeastward across fields from point just south of Calamus Ave. and west of 69th Place, showing the undeveloped condition of 69th Place (along line of fence).

April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
